PDF-Boxer

Use my version of a "box model" layout to create PDFs.
Use PDF::Boxer::SpecParser to parse a template written in the not so patented PDFML.
Suggestion: Use L<Template> to dynamically create your PDFML template. 

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

  perl Makefile.PL
  make
  make test
  make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc PDF::Boxer

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=PDF-Boxer

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/PDF-Boxer

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/PDF-Boxer

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/PDF-Boxer/


